description:
Today the bubble's raw-export path writes to Application Support/SelfieOverlayKit/RawExports/<uuid>/, which is invisible to the Files app no matter what the host does. Switch the default to Documents/SelfieOverlayKit/RawExports/<uuid>/ â€” host apps that add UIFileSharingEnabled + LSSupportsOpeningDocumentsInPlace to Info.plist will then have recordings show up in Files â†’ On My iPhone â†’ [App Name] â†’ SelfieOverlayKit/RawExports/ with zero code at the call site.

Keep Application Support available for hosts that explicitly don't want raw recordings on the Documents path (e.g., apps with strict storage discipline or apps that don't want users browsing files).

## Public API

Add to SelfieOverlayKit:

    public enum RawExportLocation: String, CaseIterable, Codable {
        /// Documents directory. Visible in the Files app when the host adds
        /// UIFileSharingEnabled and LSSupportsOpeningDocumentsInPlace to its
        /// Info.plist. Default.
        case documents
        /// Application Support directory. Sandboxed; never user-visible.
        /// Use when the host wants raw recordings hidden from the Files app.
        case applicationSupport
    }

Add to SettingsStore:

    @Published public var rawExportLocation: RawExportLocation  // default .documents

Persisted under SelfieOverlay.rawExportLocation. Reset() restores .documents.

## Wiring

OverlayController.nextRawExportDestination() switches roots based on settings.rawExportLocation:
- .documents â†’ FileManager.default.urls(for: .documentDirectory, in: .userDomainMask).first
- .applicationSupport â†’ existing path

Both append SelfieOverlayKit/RawExports/<uuid>/ as today.

## Not in scope

No new SettingsView UI element. End users don't make this choice â€” it's a developer-time decision per host app. SDK consumers set it programmatically:

    SelfieOverlayKit.shared.settings.rawExportLocation = .applicationSupport
